<title>USA: DVL to issue preferred stock to pay loans.</title>
<headline>DVL to issue preferred stock to pay loans.</headline>
<dateline>BOGOTA, N.J. 1996-09-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>DVL Inc said Wednesday that its shareholders approved the creation of a class of preferred stock to be issued to NPM Capital LLC.</p>
<p>In exchange, NPM will purchase three existing loans from other DVL creditors and provide funds to DVL to meet its payments on two other loans, the company said.</p>
<p>In addition, DVL will sell to affiliates of NPM one million shares of its common stock at $0.20 per share, and grant the affiliates NPM warrants to acquire additional shares of common stock at $0.16 a share.</p>
